$interpreted: Tica: Haven't found it yet?
Leah: Don't rush me. The forest is filled with all kinds of scents. It takes time to tell them apart.
Leah: Wow~ These flowers are so lovely!
Tica: Wait, don't pluck them!
Fatima: STOP!
Fatima: Cursed sorcerer...hmm, aren't you Ceres' tag-along?
Tica: Miss Fatima! You Panthers all look the same, so I didn't recognize you.
Tica: If you looked a little more...unique, then maybe...
Fatima: You humans are all clones of each other! NOW WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE!?
Tica: This place looks familiar, must have accidentally stepped into Panther territory again...
Fatima: That's right! Furthermore, both of you plucked my precious flowers, used as offerings to the gods!
Tica: I'm sorry~ I'm on a mission from Headmaster Ceres...
Tica: Didn't mean to trouble the Panthers, not one bit!
Leah: You know this frightening feline?
Tica: Yeah. Several years ago, there was a clash between the Panthers of Whistlewood Valley and the Rune Academy.
Tica: I was there!
Leah: Then isn't she the enemy?
Tica: No need to worry! The headmaster fixed it all up with his words of wisdom~
Leah: Then why is she all worked up?
Tica: The Panthers care very much for their territory. You were in the wrong for plucking those flowers.
Fatima: OH!
Tica: You're hurt! Wait a moment, I'll heal you with some arcane magic...
Fatima: Be gone! I need not the aid of arcane magic!
Leah: But you have trouble standing up?
Fatima: It's none of your concern. We Panthers always bring medicinal herbs with us...
Fatima: Curses, no herbs left.
Tica: Er...she's out of herbs, but won't let me heal her.
Tica: If Headmaster finds out about this incident, I'll be in detention for years!
Leah: Um......
Leah: Piece of cake. Lemme borrow that.
Fatima: Hey, what are you doing?!
Leah: I'm confident I can find your herbs! Stay here and don't move.
Tica: No kidding?
Leah: Of course! If we find those herbs, you can focus on finding that seed.
Leah: This way!
Tica: We'll help you find the herbs, then we're even...
Tica: Don't you tell Headmaster Ceres about this!
Fatima: Hmph!
